net.opentsdb.query.expression

类 IntersectionIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.opentsdb.query.expression.IntersectionIterator
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    ITimeSyncedIterator, VariableIterator

    public class IntersectionIterator
extends Object
implements ITimeSyncedIterator, VariableIterator
    This class handles taking a set of queries and their results and iterates over each series in each set with time alignment after computing the intersection of all sets.

    The iterator performs the following: - calculates the intersection of all queries based on the tags or query tags and optionally the aggregated tags. - any series that are not members of ever set are kicked out (and logged). - series are aligned across queries so that expressions can operate over them. - series are also time aligned and maintain alignment during iteration.

    The current_values map will map the expression "variables" to the proper iterator for each serie's array. E.g. <"A", [1, 2, 3, 4]> <"B", [1, 2, 3, 4]>

    So to use it's you simply fetch the result map, call hasNext() and next() to iterate and in a for loop, iterate getSeriesSize() times to get all of the current values. For efficiency, call getResults() once before iterating, then on each call to next() you can just iterate over the same result map again as the values will be updated.

    从以下版本开始:
    2.3

    • 构造器详细资料

      • IntersectionIterator

        public IntersectionIterator(String id,
                            Map<String,ITimeSyncedIterator> results,
                            boolean intersect_on_query_tagks,
                            boolean include_agg_tags)
        Ctor to create the expression lock-step iterator from a set of query results. If the results map is empty, then the ctor will complete but the results map will be empty and calls to hasNext() will always return false.
        参数:
        results - The query results to store
        intersect_on_query_tagks - Whether or not to include only the query specified tags during intersection
        include_agg_tags - Whether or not to include aggregated tags during intersection
        抛出:
        IllegalDataException - if, after computing the intersection, no results would be left.

      • getResults

        public Map<String,ExpressionDataPoint[]> getResults()
        从接口复制的说明: VariableIterator
        Returns a map of variable names to result series. You can maintain the reference returned without having to call getResults() on every iteration. Calling VariableIterator.next() will simply update the ExpressionDataPoint array. The implementation may return a null map if there weren't any results available. Always all VariableIterator.hasNext() before getting the results.
        指定者:
        getResults 在接口中 VariableIterator
        返回:
        a map of values that will change on each iteration
